-- Turkey Electricity Producers Fall on Report Gas Prices May Rise
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-04-03T12:43:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/turkey-electricity-producers-fall-on-report-gas-prices-may-rise.html
Turkish electricity companies
including  Aksa Enerji Uretim AS (AKSEN)  and  Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR) 
fell after Haberturk reported Turkey may increase natural  gas
prices  by an additional 15 percent, raising production costs.  Aksa plunged 3.3 percent to 3.79 liras and Akenerji dropped
0.9 percent to 2.12 liras at 3:15 p.m. in Istanbul. The index of
five Turkish  electricity producers  fell 1.1 percent, compared
with a 0.8 percent gain in the overall  Istanbul Stock Exchange
National 100 Index. (XU100)   Turkey raised gas prices by 18.7 percent on April 1 and may
increase them another 15 percent to stem losses at state-run
pipeline company Boru Hatlari Ile Petrol Tasima AS, Haberturk
reported, citing unidentified Energy Ministry officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
